in the case of the TM-polarization, in a\nmaterial with a high conductivity, light refracts in a \"wrong\" direction (at\nall positive optical parameters) due to a surface current. In the case of the\nTE-polarization, light refracts only in a \"right\" direction.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 12 Oct 2016 16:32:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-13"}
