perfect zero knowledge analogue of the celebrated sumcheck protocol [LFKN92],\nby leveraging both succinct constraint detection and low-degree testing. The\nsecond algorithm exploits the recursive structure of the PCPs of Proximity to\nshow that small-support constraints are \"locally\" spanned by a small number of\nsmall-support constraints.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 12 Oct 2016 17:39:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-13"}
