e that\nradiation from the central source alone cannot explain the observed\nhigh-ionization spectrum. Shocks between the radio-jet and the ambient gas are\nvery likely an additional source of excitation. We conclude that NGC 4388 is a\nprime laboratory to study the interplay between all these mechanisms.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 13 Oct 2016 03:26:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-12-14"}
